'''''Guderian''''' is a 1987 video game published by [[Avalon Hill|The Avalon Hill Game Company]].

==Gameplay==
''Guderian'' is a game in which the German drive on [[Smolensk]] during 1941 is simulated.<ref name="CGW40"/>

==Reception==
William H. Harrington reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "''Guderian'' is a very playable game with options that help gamers avoid some of the complexity and lugubrious pace of other products."<ref name="CGW40">{{cite magazine |last=Harrington |first=William H. |title=Guderian |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=October 1987 |volume=1 |issue=40 |pages=30, 61}}</ref>

